## Lakebase: Autoscaling-only — strip legacy Provisioned/Database-Instance-API code paths

Context: the runtime auth helper and the admin Lakebase metadata
lookup both still carried "try legacy Database Instance API first,
fall back to the Postgres Autoscaling API" plumbing. OntoBricks only
ever runs against Autoscaling projects (every Lakebase instance
created after 2026-03-12 is Autoscaling, including the
``ontobricks-test`` dev sandbox), so the legacy path is dead weight
that mostly serves to mask configuration mistakes — and silently
broke when the dev sandbox was bound to an Autoscaling-only project
that ``list_database_instances`` cannot see.

The user directive is unambiguous: only Autoscaling can be leveraged
here. This change removes every reference to the legacy
``WorkspaceClient.database.list_database_instances`` and
``generate_database_credential`` APIs from the runtime + admin code.

### LakebaseAuth (``src/back/core/databricks/LakebaseAuth.py``)

- ``instance_name`` now resolves the project_id via the Postgres API
  endpoint walk (``GET /api/2.0/postgres/projects`` → branches →
  endpoints, match ``status.hosts.host`` / ``read_only_host``
  against ``PGHOST``). Misses raise a single ``ValidationError``
  pointing at "the bundle is binding the wrong project" — no
  fallback / retry.
- ``password()`` mints exclusively via
  ``POST /api/2.0/postgres/credentials`` scoped to the endpoint
  resource discovered above. The legacy mint path
  (``WorkspaceClient.database.generate_database_credential``) and
  the "legacy not_found → Postgres API retry" plumbing are gone.
- ``DATABASE_INSTANCE_NAME`` env override removed — without legacy
  resolution it could not short-circuit anything (the endpoint walk
  must still happen for the mint).
- Helpers ``_lookup_via_database_instances``,
  ``_mint_via_database_instances``, ``_looks_like_instance_not_found``
  deleted.

### SettingsService (``src/back/objects/domain/SettingsService.py``)

- ``_lakebase_instance_metadata`` no longer iterates
  ``w.database.list_database_instances()``. New helper
  ``_find_autoscaling_endpoint_for_host`` walks the Postgres API and
  returns ``(project_id, primary_host, read_only_host)``; the
  payload is then enriched with branch + autoscaling CU range via
  the existing ``_lakebase_branch_info``.
- Provisioned-only fields (``capacity``, ``pg_version``,
  ``node_count``) are returned as empty so the admin UI degrades to
  ``—`` placeholders for them; the autoscaling CU range is the
  Autoscaling-native replacement and was already wired through
  ``_lakebase_branch_info``.
- Removed dead helpers ``_enum_short`` / ``_pg_version_short`` —
  they only existed to format Provisioned SDK enums for the UI and
  are no longer called from anywhere.

### Tests

- ``tests/test_lakebase_auth.py`` — rewritten for the Autoscaling-
  only contract: ``instance_name`` resolves via Postgres API only
  (legacy ``list_database_instances`` is wired to ``AssertionError``
  in every test to prove it is never called), ``password()`` mints
  via Postgres API only, caching + invalidation behaviour pinned,
  ``PGAPPNAME`` regression preserved. Net change: 14 legacy +
  fallback tests removed, 10 Autoscaling-only tests in their place.
- ``tests/test_settings_lakebase_tier.py`` — added
  ``TestLakebaseInstanceMetadataPostgresApi`` (3 tests) covering the
  new endpoint walk + payload shape; the legacy SDK call is wired to
  ``AssertionError`` in the fake workspace to lock the ban in.

Modified files
- ``src/back/core/databricks/LakebaseAuth.py``
- ``src/back/objects/domain/SettingsService.py``
- ``tests/test_lakebase_auth.py``
- ``tests/test_settings_lakebase_tier.py``

Test result: ``pytest`` — 1892 passed in 59.35s.

